[[Image:BRL Light.JPG|thumb]] The '''Benelux Racing League Light''' is a race-class that is mostly run in [[Belgium]] and [[The Netherlands]]. It serves as the development series of the [[BRL V6]].
==The car== All the cars in the series are the same. They use the body and a tubular chassis of a [[Ford Focus (International)|Ford Focus]]. The engine is a 240[[Horsepower|hp]], 2.3[[Liter|L]] [[Ford Duratec]]. The cars have rearwheel drive. The weight of the car is 825[[kg]]. The series uses [[Dunlop Tyres|Dunlop]] slicks.
