{{Multiple issues| {{Notability|Events|date=June 2014}} {{Unreferenced|date=May 2017}}}} {{infobox music festival | music_festival_name = Boundary Waters Blues Festival | image = | caption = | location = | years_active = 2001-present | founders = Michael Jankovec and Deb Pettit | dates = Weekend before Labor Day weekend | genre = [[Blues]] | website = http://elyblues.com/ }}
'''Boundary Waters Blues Festival''' was established in 2001 by [[Michael Jankovec]], host of a [[blues]] radio show in [[Ely, Minnesota|Ely]], [[Minnesota]] and Deb Pettit and Doug Brown, of Timber Wolf Lodge. He continues to run the festival, which occurs on the weekend before the [[Labor Day]] weekend. The official host of the event is [[Boundary Waters Radio]].
Since its conception the Boundary Waters Blues Festival has showcased over 30 different blues acts, including [[Little Milton]], [[Bobby Rush (musician)|Bobby Rush]], [[Ronnie Baker Brooks]], [[Reneé Austin]], [[Larry McCray]], [[Ernie Lancaster]], [[Floyd Miles]], [[George "Mojo" Buford]], [[Jimmy D. Lane]], Peach, [[Chris Beard (singer)|Chris Beard]], [[Kelly Richey]], Big Walter Smith, [[Rita Chiarelli]], [[Fruteland Jackson]], [[Diunna Greenleaf]], Rico McFarland, and [[Johnny Rawls]].
==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== *[http://www.boundarywatersradio.com/ Boundary Waters Radio]
