==Events== * [[506]] &ndash; [[Alaric II]], eighth king of the [[Visigoths]] promulgates the [[Breviary of Alaric]] (''Breviarium Alaricianum'' or ''Lex Romana Visigothorum''), a collection of "[[Roman law]]". * [[880]] &ndash; [[Battle of Luneberg Heath|Battle of Lüneburg Heath]]: King [[Louis III of France|Louis III]] is defeated by the Norse [[Great Heathen Army]] at [[Lüneburg Heath]] in [[Saxony]]. * [[962]] &ndash; ''[[Translatio imperii]]'': [[Pope John XII]] crowns [[Otto I, Holy Roman Emperor]], the first [[Holy Roman Emperor]] in nearly 40 years. * [[1032]] &ndash; [[Conrad II, Holy Roman Emperor]] becomes king of [[Kingdom of Burgundy|Burgundy]]. * [[1141]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Lincoln (1141)|Battle of Lincoln]], at which [[Stephen, King of England]] is defeated and captured by the allies of [[Empress Matilda]]. * [[1207]] &ndash; [[Terra Mariana]], eventually comprising present-day [[Latvia]] and [[Estonia]], is established. * [[1438]] &ndash; Nine leaders of the [[Transylvanian peasant revolt]] are executed at [[Turda|Torda]]. * [[1461]] &ndash; [[Wars of the Roses]]: The [[Battle of Mortimer's Cross]] is fought in [[Herefordshire]], England. * [[1536]] &ndash; Spaniard [[Pedro de Mendoza]] founds [[Buenos Aires|Buenos Aires, Argentina]]. * [[1645]] &ndash; [[Battle of Inverlochy (1645)|Battle of Inverlochy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portal.historicenvironment.scot/designation/BTL24 |title= Battle of Inverlochy II |publisher=Historic Environment Scotland | accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref> * [[1653]] &ndash; [[New Amsterdam]] (later renamed The City of New York) is incorporated. * [[1709]] &ndash; [[Alexander Selkirk]] is rescued after being shipwrecked on a desert island, inspiring [[Daniel Defoe]]'s adventure book ''[[Robinson Crusoe]]''. * [[1848]] &ndash; [[Mexican–American War]]: The [[Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo]] is signed. * [[1850]] &ndash; [[Brigham Young]] declares war on [[Timpanogos]] in the [[Battle at Fort Utah]]. * [[1868]] &ndash; Pro-Imperial forces [[Fall of Osaka Castle|captured]] [[Osaka Castle]] from the [[Tokugawa shogunate]] and burned it to the ground. * [[1876]] &ndash; The [[National League|National League of Professional Baseball Clubs]] of [[Major League Baseball]] is formed. * [[1887]] &ndash; In [[Punxsutawney, Pennsylvania]] the first [[Groundhog Day]] is observed. * [[1899]] &ndash; The Australian Premiers' Conference held in [[Melbourne]] decides to locate Australia's capital city, [[Canberra]], between Sydney and [[Melbourne]]. * [[1901]] &ndash; Funeral of [[Queen Victoria]]. * [[1913]] &ndash; [[Grand Central Terminal]] is opened in New York City. * [[1920]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of Tartu (Russian–Estonian)|Tartu Peace Treaty]] is signed between [[Estonia]] and Russia. * 1920 &ndash; France occupies [[Klaipėda|Memel]]. * [[1922]] &ndash; ''[[Ulysses (novel)|Ulysses]]'' by [[James Joyce]] is published. * [[1925]] &ndash; [[1925 serum run to Nome|Serum run to Nome]]: [[Dog sled]]s reach [[Nome, Alaska]] with [[diphtheria]] serum, inspiring the [[Iditarod Trail Sled Dog Race|Iditarod]] race. * [[1934]] &ndash; The [[Export-Import Bank of the United States]] is incorporated. * [[1935]] &ndash; [[Leonarde Keeler]] administers [[polygraph machine|polygraph tests]] to two murder suspects, the first time polygraph evidence was admitted in U.S. courts. * 1942 &ndash; The [[Osvald Group]] is responsible for the first, active event of [[Resistance movement|anti-Nazi resistance]] in Norway, to protest the [[inauguration]] of [[Vidkun Quisling]]. * [[1943]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The [[Battle of Stalingrad]] comes to an end when [[Red Army|Soviet]] troops accept the surrender of the last German troops in the city. * [[1959]] &ndash; Nine experienced ski hikers in the northern [[Ural Mountains]] in the [[Soviet Union]] [[Dyatlov Pass incident|die under mysterious circumstances]]. * [[1966]] &ndash; Pakistan suggests a six-point agenda with [[Kashmir]] after the [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1965]]. * [[1971]] &ndash; [[Idi Amin]] replaces [[President of Uganda|President]] [[Milton Obote]] as leader of [[Uganda]]. * 1971 &ndash; The international [[Ramsar Convention]] for the conservation and sustainable utilization of [[wetland]]s is signed in [[Ramsar, Mazandaran]], [[Iran]]. * [[1980]] &ndash; Reports surface that the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] is targeting allegedly corrupt [[United States Congress|Congressmen]] in the [[Abscam]] operation. * [[1982]] &ndash; [[1982 Hama massacre|Hama massacre]]: The government of [[Syria]] attacks the town of [[Hama]]. * [[1987]] &ndash; After the 1986 [[People Power Revolution]], the [[Philippines]] enacts a new [[Constitution of the Philippines|constitution]]. * [[1989]] &ndash; [[Soviet–Afghan War]]: The last [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] armoured column [[Soviet withdrawal from Afghanistan|leaves]] [[Kabul]]. * [[1990]] &ndash; [[Apartheid]]: [[F. W. de Klerk]] [[Speech at the Opening of the Parliament of South Africa, 1990|announces]] the unbanning of the [[African National Congress]] and promises to release [[Nelson Mandela]]. * [[2000]] &ndash; First [[digital cinema]] projection in Europe (Paris) realized by Philippe Binant with the DLP CINEMA technology developed by [[Texas Instruments]]. * [[2004]] &ndash; Swiss [[tennis]] player [[Roger Federer]] becomes the [[List of ATP number 1 ranked singles players|No. 1 ranked men's singles player]], a position he will hold for a record [[ATP World Tour records#ATP Rankings|237 weeks]]. * [[2005]] &ndash; The [[Government of Canada]] introduces the ''[[Civil Marriage Act]]''. This legislation would become law on [[July 20]], 2005, legalizing [[same-sex marriage]]. * [[2007]] &ndash; Police officer [[Filippo Raciti]] is killed when a clash breaks out in the Sicily derby between Catania and Palermo, in the [[Serie A]], the top flight of Italian football. This event led to major changes in stadium regulations in Italy. * [[2012]] &ndash; The ferry [[MV Rabaul Queen]] sinks off the coast of [[Papua New Guinea]] near the [[Finschhafen District]], with an estimated 146-165 dead.
