{{Unreferenced|date=October 2014}}
[[File:2008-08 Halle 02.jpg|thumb|Halle Opera House]]
The '''Halle Opera House''' ({{Lang-de|'''Opernhaus Halle'''}}) is an [[opera house]] in [[Halle, Saxony-Anhalt]]. Originally named the '''Halle Town Theatre'''  ({{Lang-de|'''Stadttheater von Halle'''}}), the theatre was built in 1886. A bomb attack on 31 March 1945 destroyed much of the original building. Restorative work ensued a few years later, and the theatre reopened in 1951 under the name '''Landestheater Halle'''. In January 1992 it was renamed to its current title. The theatre is currently used for performances of [[opera]], [[ballet]], [[Play (theatre)|play]]s, and [[orchestra]]l concerts. It is also the main performance venue for the annual summer [[Handel Festival, Halle|Handel Festival]] held in the city.

